3. Brutorum, Cassiorum, etc. It was the fashion at this time to cherish the busts, especially of Republican heroes. The feeling seems to have been about as deep as that for the Pretender in our own country when all hope for his cause had been abandoned, and we may imagine the Romans indulging in the same kind of observanee to their heroes
